{{ 'dev-cart-drawer.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'dev-cart-drawer.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>

{%- comment -%} Fixed design tokens from Figma — not merchant-controlled {%- endcomment -%}
<style>
  .cart-drawer {

    /* The FIXED width of the drawer panel ("Cart/Order" 45058:2048) — this is the
       overlay's own width token, NOT the site's centred page container. On mobile the
       panel is full-bleed, so it is not applied there. */
    --container-max: 568px;

    --section-px: 32px;
    --section-px-mobile: 16px;
    /* Mobile header row keeps 24px of horizontal padding while the body drops to 16px
       (44840:5860) — extra breathing room around the close button. Intentional. */
    --header-px-mobile: 24px;

    /* Desktop floats the panel 16px off the viewport edge (outer wrapper 45058:2164).
       Mobile is a bottom sheet: flush left/right/bottom, gap at the top. */
    --drawer-inset: 16px;
    --sheet-top-gap: 32px;

    --radius-drawer: 32px;
    --radius-drawer-mobile: 16px;
    --radius-card: 16px;
    --radius-image: 16px;
    --radius-badge: 8px;
    --radius-cta: 60px;
    --radius-payment: 2px;

    /* Desktop/Title 3 vs Mobile/Title 3 — the mobile artboard states its own size,
       so it wins over a scale factor. */
    --font-heading-size: 32px;
    --font-heading-size-mobile: 24px;
    --font-heading-weight: 500;
    --font-heading-lh: 1.2;

    --font-body-lh: 1.4;
    --font-size-title: 18px;
    --font-size-title-mobile: 14px;
    --font-size-option: 16px;
    --font-size-option-mobile: 14px;
    --font-size-price: 16px;
    --font-size-remove: 14px;
    --font-size-remove-mobile: 13px;
    --font-size-badge: 14px;
    --font-size-cta: 18px;
    --font-size-payment: 14px;
    --weight-medium: 500;
    --weight-bold: 700;

    --spacing-2xs: 2px;
    --spacing-xs: 4px;
    --spacing-sm: 8px;
    --spacing-md: 16px;
    --spacing-lg: 24px;
    --spacing-xl: 32px;

    --image-size: 80px;
    --image-size-mobile: 64px;
    --icon-size: 24px;

    /* Badge icons are stroked #666666 on the Figma layers — a muted grey that is
       deliberately not the body text colour. */
    --icon-muted: #666666;
  }
</style>

{%- liquid
  assign cta_alpha = block.settings.cta_opacity | divided_by: 100.0
  assign cta_fill = block.settings.cta_color | color_modify: 'alpha', cta_alpha

  assign backdrop_alpha = block.settings.backdrop_opacity | divided_by: 100.0
  assign backdrop_fill = block.settings.backdrop_color | color_modify: 'alpha', backdrop_alpha

  assign checkout_url = block.settings.checkout_url
  if checkout_url == blank
    assign checkout_url = '/checkout'
  endif

  # Where "Continue shopping" sends an empty basket. routes.* (not a hardcoded
  # '/collections/all') because a localised storefront serves it under a locale prefix.
  assign continue_url = block.settings.continue_url
  if continue_url == blank
    assign continue_url = routes.all_products_collection_url
  endif

  assign is_open = 'false'
  if block.settings.open_on_load
    assign is_open = 'true'
  endif

  assign heading_id = 'cart-drawer-heading'
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  The overlay. id="cart-drawer" is a contract, not a preference: dev-site-header's
  cart trigger carries aria-controls="cart-drawer" and looks this element up by id
  before it will preventDefault and open a drawer at all.

  Closed by default: aria-hidden + inert are rendered server-side so the drawer is
  never focusable or announced before the JS runs. Open state lives in exactly one
  place — [data-open] on this root — so it can be forced open with plain JS.

  It lives as a block of dev-site-header (rather than a section of its own) so one
  configuration serves every template, and so it always ships with the trigger that
  opens it.

  That is where it is CONFIGURED. It is NOT where it lives at runtime: this markup lands
  inside #header-group, which hides on scroll down with a transform, and a transformed
  ancestor becomes the containing block for its position:fixed descendants — which turned
  `inset: 0` from "fill the viewport" into "fill the header" and collapsed the whole overlay
  to a strip off the top of the screen. dev-cart-drawer.js therefore moves this element to
  <body> on init, and the full reasoning lives in the `portal` comment there. Do not assume
  the rendered position is the final one, and do not re-add a containing block to it.

  The cart routes ride on the root as data attributes rather than being hardcoded in the
  JS (the same contract dev-main-product uses): a localised storefront serves them under
  a locale prefix, and "/cart/change.js" would 404 there.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div
  id="cart-drawer"
  class="cart-drawer"
  data-open="{{ is_open }}"
  data-cart-change-url="{{ routes.cart_change_url }}"
  data-cart-url="{{ routes.cart_url }}"
  {%- unless block.settings.open_on_load %} aria-hidden="true" inert{% endunless %}
  style="
    --bg: {{ block.settings.background_color }};
    --color: {{ block.settings.text_color }};
    --accent: {{ cta_fill }};
    --pt: {{ block.settings.padding_top }}px;
    --pb: {{ block.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
    --card-bg: {{ block.settings.card_color }};
    --badge-bg: {{ block.settings.badge_color }};
    --border-header: {{ block.settings.header_divider_color }};
    --border-header-mobile: {{ block.settings.header_divider_color_mobile }};
    --border-footer: {{ block.settings.footer_divider_color }};
    --cta-color: {{ block.settings.cta_text_color }};
    --backdrop: {{ backdrop_fill }};
  "
  {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
>
  <div class="cart-drawer__backdrop" data-cart-drawer-close></div>

  <div
    class="cart-drawer__panel"
    role="dialog"
    aria-modal="true"
    aria-labelledby="{{ heading_id }}"
  >
    <div class="cart-drawer__header">
      {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
        <h2 class="cart-drawer__heading" id="{{ heading_id }}">{{ block.settings.heading }}</h2>
      {%- endif -%}

      <button
        type="button"
        class="cart-drawer__close"
        data-cart-drawer-close
        aria-label="{{ block.settings.close_label | escape }}"
      >
        <svg class="cart-drawer__icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
<path d="M7 17L17 7M7 7L17 17" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="cart-drawer__content">
      {%- if cart.item_count > 0 -%}
        <ul class="cart-drawer__items">
          {%- for item in cart.items -%}
            {%- liquid
              assign item_alt = item.title | escape
              assign item_src = item.image | image_url: width: 240
            -%}
            <li class="cart-drawer__item">
              <div class="cart-drawer__item-detail">
                <div class="cart-drawer__item-media">
                  {%- if item.image != blank -%}
                    <a class="cart-drawer__item-image-link" href="{{ item.url }}">
                      {{
                        item_src
                        | image_tag:
                          loading: 'lazy',
                          widths: '64, 80, 128, 160, 240',
                          sizes: '(max-width: 768px) 64px, 80px',
                          alt: item_alt,
                          class: 'cart-drawer__item-image'
                      }}
                    </a>
                  {%- endif -%}

                  <div class="cart-drawer__item-info">
                    <h3 class="cart-drawer__item-title">
                      <a class="cart-drawer__item-title-link" href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.product.title | escape }}</a>
                    </h3>

                    {%- for option in item.options_with_values -%}
                      {%- if option.value != blank -%}
                        <p class="cart-drawer__item-option">
                          <span class="cart-drawer__item-option-name">{{ option.name | escape }}:</span>
                          <span class="cart-drawer__item-option-value">{{ option.value | escape }}</span>
                        </p>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    {%- endfor -%}

                    <p class="cart-drawer__item-qty">
                      <span class="cart-drawer__item-qty-label">{{ block.settings.quantity_label | escape }}:</span>
                      <span class="cart-drawer__item-qty-value">{{ item.quantity }}</span>
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="cart-drawer__item-actions">
                  <p class="cart-drawer__item-price">{{ item.line_price | money }}</p>
                  {%- comment -%}
                    Still a real link to /cart/change, so removing a line works with JS off — it
                    just costs a page load and lands on /cart, which is the browser doing exactly
                    what the link says. The JS upgrades it into a cart change made in place; it is
                    an upgrade on the link, never a replacement for it.

                    It removes BY KEY, not by line number. The line number in url_to_remove is a
                    position, and positions shift the moment anything above them is removed — the
                    key names this line whatever happens to the ones around it.
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  <a
                    class="cart-drawer__item-remove"
                    href="{{ item.url_to_remove }}"
                    data-cart-remove
                    data-line-key="{{ item.key }}"
                  >
                    {{- block.settings.remove_label | escape -}}
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>

              {%- comment -%}
                The badges belong to the PRODUCT on this line, not to the drawer. They used to be
                blocks of this drawer, which meant one hardcoded row painted onto every line in the
                basket: add a pillow next to the duvet and the pillow would claim to be a
                hypoallergenic tree-fibre duvet too. Now each line reads its own product's badges,
                and a product with none simply shows none.

                An uploaded image wins over the icon. The bundled icons are inline SVG on
                currentColor — they inherit the drawer's text colour, which an <img> cannot do — so
                the icon stays the default and the image is the override, not the other way round.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              {%- assign badges = item.product.metafields.larke.cart_badges.value -%}
              {%- if badges.size > 0 -%}
                <ul class="cart-drawer__badges">
                  {%- for badge in badges -%}
                    {%- if badge.label.value != blank -%}
                      <li class="cart-drawer__badge">
                        {%- if badge.image.value != blank -%}
                          <img
                            class="cart-drawer__badge-image"
                            src="{{ badge.image.value | image_url: width: 72 }}"
                            alt=""
                            width="24"
                            height="24"
                            loading="lazy"
                            aria-hidden="true"
                          >
                        {%- else -%}
                          {%- render 'dev-cart-drawer-badge-icon', icon: badge.icon.value -%}
                        {%- endif -%}
                        <span class="cart-drawer__badge-label">{{ badge.label.value | escape }}</span>
                      </li>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </ul>
              {%- endif -%}
            </li>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </ul>

      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          An empty basket is otherwise a dead end: the only other control in the drawer is the
          close button, so the message alone tells the shopper the bad news and nothing else.
          A real <a> to a collection, not a "dismiss the drawer" button — it gives them somewhere
          to go, and it still works with JS off, which a close-the-panel button cannot.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="cart-drawer__empty-state">
          <p class="cart-drawer__empty">{{ block.settings.empty_text | escape }}</p>

          {%- if block.settings.continue_label != blank -%}
            {%- render 'dev-button',
              variant: 'filled',
              label: block.settings.continue_label,
              link: continue_url,
              full: true,
              class: 'cart-drawer__continue'
            -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>

    <div class="cart-drawer__footer">
      {%- comment -%}
        Guarded on the basket having something in it, not just on the label being set. An empty
        basket used to render "Checkout Securely" — the most prominent control in the drawer
        pointing at a checkout with nothing to buy.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if cart.item_count > 0 and block.settings.checkout_label != blank -%}
        <a class="cart-drawer__checkout dev-btn dev-btn--ghost dev-btn--full" href="{{ checkout_url }}">
          <span class="cart-drawer__checkout-label dev-btn__label">{{ block.settings.checkout_label | escape }}</span>
          <svg class="cart-drawer__icon dev-btn__icon" viewBox="329.5 18.5 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
<path d="M341.5 33.5V35.5M335.5 39.5H347.5C348.605 39.5 349.5 38.6046 349.5 37.5V31.5C349.5 30.3954 348.605 29.5 347.5 29.5H335.5C334.395 29.5 333.5 30.3954 333.5 31.5V37.5C333.5 38.6046 334.395 39.5 335.5 39.5ZM345.5 29.5V25.5C345.5 23.2909 343.709 21.5 341.5 21.5C339.291 21.5 337.5 23.2909 337.5 25.5V29.5H345.5Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg>
        </a>
      {%- endif -%}

      <div class="cart-drawer__payment">
        {%- if block.settings.payment_label != blank -%}
          <p class="cart-drawer__payment-label">{{ block.settings.payment_label | escape }}</p>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          Two sources, chosen by the "Payment icons" setting (block.settings.payment_icons_source):
          - dynamic (default): shop.enabled_payment_types -> Shopify's own icon set,
            always matching what is actually enabled at checkout, zero maintenance.
          - custom: the eight marks exported from the Figma artboard, in artboard
            order, pixel-matched to the owner's brand artwork. The last mark is filed
            in Figma as a second "Amex" but is a blue Shop Pay mark (flagged in the
            Brief) — drawn exactly as exported and labelled for what it depicts.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <ul class="cart-drawer__payment-icons">
          {%- if block.settings.payment_icons_source == 'dynamic' -%}
            {%- for type in shop.enabled_payment_types -%}
              <li class="cart-drawer__payment-item">{{ type | payment_type_svg_tag: class: 'cart-drawer__payment-icon' }}</li>
            {%- endfor -%}
          {%- else -%}
          <li class="cart-drawer__payment-item"><svg class="cart-drawer__payment-icon" viewBox="0 0 35 20" width="35" height="20" fill="none" role="img" aria-label="Visa">
<g id="Visa-cd-visa">
